1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Are you tired of moderating spam comments on your website?

2
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:06,560
Let's explore the discussion settings so that you can personalize your site and make

3
00:00:07,640 --> 00:00:10,640
comment moderation even easier.

4
00:00:09,640 --> 00:00:12,640
I'll be navigating around my food blog, but feel free to pull up your own site and make

5
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:17,280
changes there as we go.

6
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:19,160
To start, we'll hover over settings on the left navigation bar and then click on Discussion.

7
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:25,680
The first thing you see here is default post settings.

8
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:29,080
I'm going to check that first option, which allows WordPress to notify linked sites if I

9
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:33,840
mention them in my posts.

10
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:35,760
I also want to be notified if another blog links to my post, so I'm going to check

11
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:39,840
the second box down also.

12
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:42,160
That allows for notifications of trackbacks or pingbacks.

13
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:46,320
The third box is pretty important in my opinion.

14
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:49,480
This is where I can enable or disable comments as a whole.

15
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:53,040
But in my case, or for my food blog, I love a good conversation, so I'm going to allow

16
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:57,480
comments by checking this box.

17
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,800
Now in my food blog, if I enable comments, you'll see them right below the post.

18
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:05,520
And if I disable comments, you'll see that there's no place to leave one.

19
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:10,200
You can also make these changes on a post by post basis.

20
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Just scroll down to the discussion meta box and enable or disable comments right from there.

21
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:21,160
Other comment settings determine how WordPress will handle comments when they're posted.

22
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
The first option requires each commenter to leave a name and email address with each

23
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:31,200
comment.

24
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:32,200
The second option requires that commenter to be logged in.

25
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:36,120
The benefit of checking these boxes is that you're adding in some extra friction when

26
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:40,640
someone leaves a comment.

27
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,600
But the limitation is that you might actually turn away some visitors from commenting.

28
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:47,680
For my food blog, I'm going to check the first box, but also let unregistered visitors

29
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:52,160
comment too.

30
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:53,960
If I don't receive an unmanageable number of comments on my blog, I'm not going to check

31
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:58,080
that third box, which would turn comments off after a certain number of days.

32
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:03,360
Fourth option gives the comment author the option to opt in for cookies.

33
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
I'm a big fan of transparency, so I'm going to check that fourth box.

34
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:12,280
The next option allows other commenters to respond to a visitor.

35
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,840
I love this idea because it allows your visitors to have a conversation with each other.

36
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:21,760
The default is a nest of five comments deep.

37
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
When I activate this feature, now on my food blog, different visitors can continue the

38
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:29,640
conversation and reply to each other.

39
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:32,360
You can change that number to be less or more, depending on if you think it'll help

40
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:36,320
with moderation or add to the conversation.

41
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:39,960
And if you have a ton of comments on a post, you can use these options to moderate how many

42
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:44,620
show up at a time and the order.

43
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:48,720
If we move on to email me whenever, you'll see you have two options.

44
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:52,480
To get an email notification, if someone posts a comment, and to get an email notification

45
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:58,160
if a comment is held for moderation, feel free to check either one of those if you would

46
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,920
like to be notified via email.

47
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:05,720
Next, you'll see before a comment appears.

48
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,840
This allows you to moderate or approve comments before they even appear on your website.

49
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,000
You can also choose to automatically approve comments from authors who you've already previously

50
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,200
approved.

51
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:20,200
To help reduce spam comments, and since I don't receive a ton to begin with, I'm going

52
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:24,760
to choose to manually approve my comments.

53
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:27,520
I can always change this if it becomes too time consuming or delays the conversation in

54
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:32,840
the comments.

55
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:34,640
Comment moderation and comment blacklist allow you to target specific words, terms, and links

56
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:40,160
in comments.

57
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:41,440
When these targeted items are found in a comment, you can set that to be forced moderation or

58
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:46,720
to be blacklisted.

59
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:48,160
This can help identifying control spam.

60
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:50,720
So for instance, I can block certain words that often show up, like "sale" or even "try

61
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:57,120
this" or certain IP addresses.

62
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:59,760
I can later check my spam comments to make sure a real comment didn't get filtered out.

63
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:05,480
And onto the last part of discussion settings are avatars.

64
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:09,560
You can select whether or not to show a commenter's avatar when they comment on a post.

65
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:14,400
If you choose to display avatars, you can also control what type of avatar is displayed.

66
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,680
That includes the rating to make sure that it could be suitable for all audiences or

67
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:24,280
even more mature.

68
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:25,760
And then also what the avatar looks like.

69
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:27,880
I'm going to go ahead and pick that retro option because that's my favorite.

70
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:33,120
And now you can see what that retro avatar looks like when visitors leave a comment on

71
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,600
my blog.

72
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:38,600
Okay, that looks great, so I'm going to make sure I go back and hit save changes.

73
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:44,480
You've now gone through and personalized all of your discussion settings.

